iency of the parallel multigrid algorithms, and finally applications of RMT for the numerical solution of the incompressible Navier Stokes equations. Potential readers are graduate students and researchers working in applied and numerical mathematics as well as multigrid practitioners and software programmers. ContentsIntroduction to multigridRobust multigrid techniqueParallel multigrid methodsApplications of multigrid methods in computational fluid dynamics  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aBoundary value problems. 0aNumerical analysis. 0aUncertaintyxMathematical models. 4aBlackbox. 4aDiskretisierung. 4aMehrgitterverfahren. 4aNumerische Strömungssimulation. 4aRandwertproblem. 7aMATHEMATICS / Numerical Analysis.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z978311071954308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017z978311062526408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Mathematics 2017z9783110548204oZDB-23-DMA0 cEPUBz97831105376280 cprintz978311053755040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311053926440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110539264423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110539264.jpg  a978-3-11-062526-4  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017b2017  a978-3-11-071954-3  DG Plus eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MTPY  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MTPY  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2017  aZDB-23-DMAb2017